# Object Detection Annotation — Bounding Box Dataset

Bounding box and class label annotation for AI object detection model training.

## Overview
This repository documents object detection annotation work — applying bounding boxes, confidence zones, and class labels across image batches. Output datasets are structured for use with standard object detection frameworks.

## Tools Used
- Manual bounding box annotation
- Class label schema design
- QA review pipeline

## Annotation Format
```json
{
  "image_id": "frame_0042",
  "annotations": [
    {
      "label": "PART_A",
      "confidence": 0.94,
      "bbox": [40, 38, 70, 55],
      "format": "x, y, width, height"
    },
    {
      "label": "PART_B",
      "confidence": 0.87,
      "bbox": [140, 50, 80, 65]
    }
  ]
}
```

## QA Process
1. Initial annotation pass
2. Peer review of edge cases
3. Confidence threshold validation
4. Final dataset export

